Vestar Capital Partners, Inc.: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 28, 2017 11:26 PM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of Vestar Capital Partners, Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Vestar Capital Partners, Inc. is a private equity firm specializing in growth capital investments, management buyouts, buyins, acquisitions or recapitalizations of public and private companies, middle market, corporate divestitures, and family successions and partnerships in mid sized companies. The firm invests in a wide variety of industries with a focus on consumer, business services, diversified industries, healthcare, financial, and digital media and communications sector. Within the financial sector, it prefers to invest in financial services, specialty finance, insurance, savings management, leasing, and factoring. Within the consumer sector, the firm targets food products, apparel, h...
Vestar Capital Partners, Inc. is a private equity firm specializing in growth capital investments, management buyouts, buyins, acquisitions or recapitalizations of public and private companies, middle market, corporate divestitures, and family successions and partnerships in mid sized companies. The firm invests in a wide variety of industries with a focus on consumer, business services, diversified industries, healthcare, financial, and digital media and communications sector. Within the financial sector, it prefers to invest in financial services, specialty finance, insurance, savings management, leasing, and factoring. Within the consumer sector, the firm targets food products, apparel, household goods, retail and services.  Within diversified industries sector, the firm seeks to invest from traditional industrial products and services to aerospace, manufacturing, transportation, logistics, consumer services, energy and industrial services, packaging, chemicals, software, natural resources, and alternative energy. Within healthcare, it focuses on digital health media, informatics, providers, services, and medical technology.  Within media and communication sector, it seeks to invest in publishing companies, cable and radio networks, and telecommunications and marketing services. The firm invests around the globe with focus in the North America (specifically U.S.) and Europe. It prefers to invest $2 million to $750 million.in midmarket companies with enterprise values between $100 million and $3 billion. The firm prefers to take control or minority stake in the portfolio companies. Vestar Capital Partners, Inc. was founded in 1988 and is based in New York, New York with additional offices in Denver, Colorado; and Boston, Massachusetts.
